# Bit Core [ACTIVE]
  id: bit-core
  kind: TOOL
  version: 0.1.0
  summary: Core bit language tools, file I/O, shell, and memory
  scope: agent
  immutable: true

## Tools:Bit
  ### parse
    summary: Parse .bit source text into an AST. Use this to validate .bit syntax after writing plan.bit or any .bit file. Returns the parsed structure or errors.
    params:
      - name: source
        type: string
        required: true
        description: The .bit source text to parse. Example: '# My Plan\n    [!] First task\n    [!] Second task'
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: object
        description: Parsed AST structure or error details

  ### index
    summary: Build an index from .bit source, extracting tasks (with statuses [!]/[o]/[x]), groups, entities, and validators. Use this to check task progress and validate plan structure.
    params:
      - name: source
        type: string
        required: true
        description: The .bit source text to index. Returns counts of pending/done tasks, group structure, entities found.
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: object
        description: Index with task counts, group structure, entities, and validators

  ### render
    summary: Render a .bit AST back to formatted .bit text. Use after parsing and modifying an AST to get clean output.
    params:
      - name: ast
        type: string
        required: true
        description: The AST (as JSON string) to render back to .bit text
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: string
        description: Formatted .bit text

  ### schemas
    summary: Extract entity schemas from .bit source. Returns field definitions with sigils (!required, ^indexed, @timestamp, #int, ?bool, []list, {}json, ->relation).
    params:
      - name: source
        type: string
        required: true
        description: The .bit source containing schema definitions
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: object
        description: Extracted schema field definitions with sigil annotations

  ### mutate
    summary: Apply mutations to .bit source — update task statuses, add/remove items, modify values. Use this to mark tasks as [o] in-progress or [x] complete in your plan.bit.
    params:
      - name: source
        type: string
        required: true
        description: The .bit source text to mutate and build into a store
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: object
        description: Mutated .bit store with applied changes

## Tools:Memory
  ### remember
    summary: Persist content to long-term memory. Use after completing tasks to remember key decisions, patterns discovered, and outcomes for future sessions.
    params:
      - name: content
        type: string
        required: true
        description: The content to remember — decisions, patterns, outcomes
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: string
        description: Confirmation that memory was persisted

  ### recall
    summary: Retrieve relevant memories matching a query. Use at the start of a task to check for prior context or related work.
    params:
      - name: query
        type: string
        required: true
        description: The query to search memories for
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: object
        description: Array of matching memories with relevance scores

## Tools:CICD
  ### inspect
    summary: Inspect the workspace CI/CD configuration from .bit/cicd. Returns the pipeline, providers, policies, and runtime state.
    params: []
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: object
        description: Workspace CI/CD configuration

  ### validate
    summary: Validate the workspace CI/CD configuration and report whether it is structurally safe to use.
    params: []
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: object
        description: Validation result with valid flag and any errors

  ### connect_provider
    summary: Connect a CI/CD provider to the workspace and persist it under .bit/cicd/providers.json.
    params:
      - name: kind
        type: string
        required: true
        description: Provider kind such as github_actions or local_runner
      - name: id
        type: string
        required: false
        description: Stable provider identifier. Defaults to the provider kind.
      - name: config
        type: object
        required: false
        description: Provider-specific configuration fields to persist
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: object
        description: Persisted provider plus the updated provider/state payloads

  ### status
    summary: Show the current CI/CD connection status including connected providers and last update time.
    params: []
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: object
        description: Connection status with connected providers and timestamps

## Tools:File
  ### read
    summary: Read the contents of a file at the given path in the workspace.
    params:
      - name: path
        type: string
        required: true
        description: Relative path to the file to read
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: string
        description: File contents as text

  ### write
    summary: Write content to a file at the given path in the workspace. Creates directories as needed. For .bit files, always validate with $Bit.parse after writing.
    params:
      - name: path
        type: string
        required: true
        description: Relative path to write the file
      - name: content
        type: string
        required: true
        description: The full content to write to the file
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: string
        description: Confirmation with path of written file

## Tools:Mods
  ### list
    summary: List all available dynamic mods that can be loaded into this session.
    params: []
    returns:
      - name: mods
        type: array
        description: Available mods with name, summary, and kind
      - name: count
        type: integer
        description: Number of available mods

  ### load
    summary: Load a dynamic mod into the current session, making its tools available.
    params:
      - name: name
        type: string
        required: true
        description: Name of the mod to load (from $Mods.list)
    returns:
      - name: loaded
        type: string
        description: Name of the loaded mod
      - name: tools_added
        type: integer
        description: Number of tools now available from this mod

  ### unload
    summary: Unload a dynamic mod from the current session, removing its tools.
    params:
      - name: name
        type: string
        required: true
        description: Name of the mod to unload
    returns:
      - name: unloaded
        type: string
        description: Name of the unloaded mod

## Tools:Shell
  ### run
    summary: Execute a shell command in the workspace directory and return its output.
    params:
      - name: command
        type: string
        required: true
        description: The shell command to execute
    returns:
      - name: result
        type: string
        description: Command stdout and stderr output
